

Solutions developed using this plugin follow the [Model-View-Controller|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model-view-controller] (MVC) architectural pattern and leverage the [Grails|http://grails.org/] Web Application Framework.

{quote}
"Anyone who hasn't done Rails has *no notion* whatsoever how outclassed they are. 
I only make an exception for Lift, Grails" 
                                         Uncle Bob Martin
{quote}

The Grails framework is built upon the [Groovy|http://groovy.codehaus.org/] language, which is a dynamic language for the [Java Virtual Machine|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_Virtual_Machine] (JVM). Grails is built upon proven Java technology and frameworks, most importantly [Spring|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spring_Framework] (an [Inversion of Control|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inversion_of_control] (IoC) container and application framework) and [Hibernate|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hibernate_(Java)] (an [Object Relational Mapping|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Object-relational_mapping] (ORM) library and [Java Persistence API|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_Persistence_API] (JPA) Provider).


